Nit: Subscription query param size

One sentence of description is nowhere near enough.  Also, please don't wrap your commit messages by hand.  50/72 please.
Done

we should spell this out as ServerSentEvent.  I don't think redfish uses abbreviations anywhere in the URI paths, so we should avoid them as well.

Also, isn't this URI going to conflict with other subscriptions?  What if you had a subscription with ID "SSE"
Done
If this uri were plugged into a browser it works?  I thought SSE had to be initiated by javascript?
Done

Done

typo.

?  this function seems incorrectly named, and this pattern seems odd.  wouldn't the SSE code itself map SSEConnection to ID, then we'd access the subscription entirely by ID?
